HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 188
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Nancy Dishner to
the board of directors of the Tennessee
education lottery corporation.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-51-101, provides for the creation of
the Tennessee education lottery corporation; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-51-103, provides that the governor
shall appoint seven (7) members to the board of directors of the Tennessee education lottery
corporation; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Dr. Nancy Dishner of Greeneville to serve
as a member of the board of directors of the Tennessee education lottery corporation for a term
that will expire on June 30, 2029; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Dishner serves as president and chief executive officer of the Niswonger
Foundation; she previously served as vice provost for enrollment services and director of the
Roan Scholars Leadership Program at East Tennessee State University (ETSU) and was a
tenured professor in the department of Educational Leadership and Policy Analysis; and
WHEREAS, prior to her position at ETSU, she served as a public-school teacher in
Unicoi County, having begun her career in early childhood development as a kindergarten
teacher; and
WHEREAS, an alumna of ETSU, Dr. Dishner has a Bachelor of Science degree in
Elementary Education, a master's degree in supervision and administration, and a doctorate in
administration; and
